520
00:40:05,711 --> 00:40:07,959
Prosecutors believe
this is just the tip of the iceberg,

521
00:40:07,959 --> 00:40:09,959
[Chairman Kwon Tied to Oh Kwang Jae Case?]
and that even more high-profile figures

522
00:40:09,959 --> 00:40:12,493
[Singer Jung Yun Seo, Actress Ryu Ji Eun]
are suspected of illegal involvement

523
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:14,078
[Ondam Hotel: The "Entertainment" Protocol]
with aspiring entertainers.

524
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:17,030
They intend to widen the investigation.

525
00:40:17,030 --> 00:40:22,170
Mr. Nam, who was locked up last April
for the murder of rookie actress Ms. Hwang,

526
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:26,640
has been cleared of all charges
and walked free this morning after ten months.

527
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:43,500
Petit! Petit! Petit!

528
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:46,553
My man, Tae Seop!

529
00:41:48,042 --> 00:41:51,225
I knew you had it in you.

530
00:41:51,958 --> 00:41:55,375
I already made sure the prosecutors throw
at least twenty years at Lee Yang Mi,

531
00:41:55,375 --> 00:41:57,467
so relax, all right?

532
00:41:57,467 --> 00:42:00,518
And Father looks like he'll
check out right on schedule.

533
00:42:00,518 --> 00:42:05,459
From here on, it's just us.
We back each other up and rise together.

534
00:42:05,459 --> 00:42:07,250
Right.

535
00:42:07,250 --> 00:42:10,827
Funny how the timing lined up so perfectly,
isn't it?

536
00:42:11,863 --> 00:42:14,115
The timing was so perfect,

537
00:42:14,115 --> 00:42:17,584
I did a deep dive into WR Hospital,

538
00:42:17,584 --> 00:42:21,088
where your father's doctor works.

539
00:42:26,335 --> 00:42:27,628
[VIP Ward Medical Inventory Ledger]

540
00:42:27,628 --> 00:42:28,713
See right there?

541
00:42:28,713 --> 00:42:33,428
Aspirin, ordered regularly,
all on your instructions.

542
00:42:33,428 --> 00:42:37,006
Aspirin is basically poison
for someone with kidney failure.

543
00:42:37,006 --> 00:42:39,898
So why was it being ordered like clockwork?

544
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:46,397
When the Chairman dies, they'll do an autopsy.

545
00:42:46,397 --> 00:42:49,484
Aspirin shows up in the toxicology,

546
00:42:49,484 --> 00:42:52,703
but there's nothing on the chart.

547
00:42:53,614 --> 00:42:56,623
That's malpractice

548
00:42:57,708 --> 00:43:00,002
and murder by proxy, isn't it?

549
00:43:04,667 --> 00:43:07,709
- Look, just hear me out.
- You know,

550
00:43:07,709 --> 00:43:09,943
you might actually end up

551
00:43:09,943 --> 00:43:12,931
outlasting your pretty stepmother behind bars.

552
00:43:16,216 --> 00:43:18,209
I thought you were an idiot...

553
00:43:18,209 --> 00:43:22,190
but you turned the family doctor
and tried to kill your own father.

554
00:43:24,417 --> 00:43:27,843
What the hell?
This isn't some medieval dynasty.

555
00:43:27,843 --> 00:43:30,470
All for that WR throne,

556
00:43:30,470 --> 00:43:33,493
you really outdid yourself. I'll give you that.

557
00:43:38,542 --> 00:43:40,792
Oh, come on...

558
00:43:49,171 --> 00:43:51,798
WR's already on your side,

559
00:43:51,798 --> 00:43:54,215
so why are you pulling this?

560
00:43:54,215 --> 00:43:57,250
I'm the one who's taking you

561
00:43:57,250 --> 00:44:01,939
all the way to the Blue House.
So what is your problem?

562
00:44:03,560 --> 00:44:06,563
Deep down, you know

563
00:44:06,563 --> 00:44:09,571
how incompetent you are
better than anyone else.

564
00:44:10,450 --> 00:44:14,576
You'll turn WR into a house of cards.

565
00:44:15,656 --> 00:44:19,434
I finally have WR under my heel.

566
00:44:19,434 --> 00:44:20,500
I'm not about to watch it crumble.

567
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:23,125
- You piece of shit.
- No.

568
00:44:23,125 --> 00:44:25,997
That's not it!

569
00:44:25,997 --> 00:44:28,186
Choose carefully.

570
00:44:28,186 --> 00:44:30,334
Spend the rest of your life rotting in a cell

571
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:33,512
as the man who killed his own father,

572
00:44:34,250 --> 00:44:36,927
or hold on to whatever's left

573
00:44:36,927 --> 00:44:39,393
of that empty throne.

574
00:44:50,959 --> 00:44:52,948
Sir.

575
00:44:54,250 --> 00:44:58,245
From now on,
every single decision about this Group

576
00:45:00,042 --> 00:45:03,208
goes through me.

577
00:45:16,709 --> 00:45:18,598
Petit.

578
00:45:27,216 --> 00:45:30,485
The real owner of WR

579
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:35,240
just changed.

580
00:45:48,792 --> 00:45:52,951
Standing where I've always dreamed of standing,

581
00:45:52,951 --> 00:45:56,261
so many faces flood back.

582
00:45:58,840 --> 00:46:01,933
Oh Kwang Jae, who pushed me into this world

583
00:46:02,697 --> 00:46:05,937
and plunged straight into hell,

584
00:46:08,584 --> 00:46:12,152
and the revolting eyes

585
00:46:13,417 --> 00:46:16,239
of every man who held the power.

586
00:46:16,857 --> 00:46:20,114
[Four Seasons]

587
00:46:25,959 --> 00:46:29,455
I'd like to thank the trash reporters

588
00:46:29,455 --> 00:46:32,334
who used their precious little fingers

589
00:46:32,334 --> 00:46:34,966
to manufacture my life.

590
00:46:36,004 --> 00:46:38,804
Thank you.

591
00:46:50,042 --> 00:46:51,900
And

592
00:46:53,496 --> 00:46:56,780
to Director Lee Yang Mi,

593
00:46:57,651 --> 00:47:02,494
who ripped out my beating heart
and left me with nothing but agony,

594
00:47:04,292 --> 00:47:07,707
my sincerest thanks.

595
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:21,096
That we were able to climb this far

596
00:47:22,277 --> 00:47:25,834
is all thanks to your petty rage

597
00:47:25,834 --> 00:47:28,645
and your dirty tricks.

598
00:47:44,250 --> 00:47:46,450
And

599
00:47:46,450 --> 00:47:51,293
to Bang Tae Seop,
who never threw me away, never let me die,

600
00:47:52,619 --> 00:47:56,339
even when I was just his shield,
and stood by me all the way here.

601
00:47:57,053 --> 00:47:59,801
Thank you.

602
00:48:08,709 --> 00:48:10,854
What were we even bleeding for,

603
00:48:12,626 --> 00:48:15,859
dragging ourselves,

604
00:48:18,582 --> 00:48:21,698
all the way here?

605
00:48:33,792 --> 00:48:36,546
Why did we have to survive

606
00:48:38,919 --> 00:48:41,551
every single one of those moments?

607
00:49:49,181 --> 00:49:51,116
Through every one

608
00:49:51,116 --> 00:49:53,957
of these impossible trials,

609
00:49:54,644 --> 00:49:59,296
the reason I never gave up
and made it to this stage

610
00:50:01,667 --> 00:50:04,342
is them.

611
00:50:05,233 --> 00:50:07,387
I dedicate this honor

612
00:50:10,417 --> 00:50:12,976
to them.

613
00:50:17,142 --> 00:50:19,416
Thank you.

614
00:51:36,542 --> 00:51:38,937
Congratulations.

615
00:51:42,394 --> 00:51:44,609
Chu Sang Ah.

616
00:52:24,704 --> 00:52:26,584
Make sure everything stays on track.

617
00:52:26,584 --> 00:52:28,736
Yes, sir.

618
00:52:38,367 --> 00:52:40,756
But you know what?

619
00:52:40,756 --> 00:52:44,252
Aren't you a little too young
to be Senior Secretary for Civil Affairs?

620
00:52:47,125 --> 00:52:52,024
Well, nobody said
old politics makes for good politics.

621
00:52:52,024 --> 00:52:54,137
Just like this script right here.

622
00:53:09,980 --> 00:53:12,547
My fellow citizens,

623
00:53:12,547 --> 00:53:14,973
and members of the press,

624
00:53:14,973 --> 00:53:18,866
today marks the 100th day
of our new administration.

625
00:53:18,866 --> 00:53:22,908
I'm here to reflect
on where we may have fallen short.

626
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:26,036
I'm here to reflect
on where we may have fallen short.

627
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:28,667
And to recommit ourselves to our mission.

628
00:53:28,667 --> 00:53:32,296
And to recommit ourselves to our mission.

629
00:53:32,296 --> 00:53:34,086
One-second pause.

630
00:53:34,086 --> 00:53:36,004
[Blue House, Republic of Korea]

631
00:53:36,004 --> 00:53:39,792
45 degrees right.

632
00:53:39,792 --> 00:53:41,643
And smile.

633
00:53:43,125 --> 00:53:44,681
First.

634
00:53:44,681 --> 00:53:48,395
I'd like to express my gratitude to the people.

635
00:53:48,395 --> 00:53:53,108
Thanks to your unwavering support,

636
00:53:53,108 --> 00:53:57,242
we've been able to govern without disruption.

637
00:53:58,833 --> 00:54:01,155
With the Seoam mayoral race just ten days out,

638
00:54:01,155 --> 00:54:04,074
[Doyak's Bang Tae Seop on the Trail]
former Senior Secretary Bang Tae Seop

639
00:54:04,074 --> 00:54:06,246
is leading in the polls.

640
00:54:06,246 --> 00:54:09,955
After spearheading sweeping reforms
of prosecution and law enforcement,

641
00:54:09,955 --> 00:54:12,499
Candidate Bang's approval has soared,

642
00:54:12,499 --> 00:54:14,961
and he's not just the frontrunner
for Seoam Mayor,

643
00:54:14,961 --> 00:54:16,776
[Youth Support Fuels Presidential Buzz]
he's already being talked about

644
00:54:16,776 --> 00:54:19,173
as a serious contender for the presidency.

645
00:54:19,173 --> 00:54:20,632
One last question.

646
00:54:20,632 --> 00:54:23,793
What does Chu Sang Ah mean to you?

647
00:54:23,793 --> 00:54:26,474
My wife and I have fought through

648
00:54:26,474 --> 00:54:29,478
countless hardships together.

649
00:54:29,478 --> 00:54:32,709
For someone who still has a long road ahead,

650
00:54:32,709 --> 00:54:34,988
she's my one and only ally.

651
00:54:36,838 --> 00:54:40,827
[Doyak Party, Bang Tae Seop]
We need to head in. Let's wrap it here.

652
00:54:41,657 --> 00:54:42,751
Thank you.

653
00:54:42,751 --> 00:54:44,667
Thank you.

654
00:54:44,667 --> 00:54:48,710
Oh, by the way,
did you hear about the WR family?

655
00:54:53,940 --> 00:54:54,958
[WR Chairman Kwon Regains Consciousness,
Signaling Return]

656
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:58,553
[Second son Kwon Jong Il rumored to return,
replacing Director Lee Yang Mi]

657
00:54:58,553 --> 00:55:02,125
WR Group Chairman Kwon Se Myeong,
one of Korea's biggest names in business,

658
00:55:02,125 --> 00:55:05,866
has reportedly woken up
after his long fight with illness.

659
00:55:05,866 --> 00:55:08,222
There are also reports
that his second son, Kwon Jong Il,

660
00:55:08,222 --> 00:55:10,827
is stepping back into management,

661
00:55:10,827 --> 00:55:15,278
and all eyes are
on WR Group's leadership shakeup.

662
00:55:28,408 --> 00:55:34,370
[Director Lee Yang Mi to be Released
via Special Pardon on the 20th]

663
00:55:44,803 --> 00:55:48,862
[Caller ID Restricted]

664
00:55:57,211 --> 00:55:59,311
This is Cheongseong Penitentiary.

665
00:55:59,311 --> 00:56:02,867
This call may be monitored.

666
00:56:11,626 --> 00:56:13,836
Chu Sang Ah.

667
00:56:27,346 --> 00:56:29,918
I'll be seeing you

668
00:56:29,918 --> 00:56:31,729
very soon.

669
00:56:54,039 --> 00:56:55,549
[Waiting Room: Chu Sang Ah]

670
00:57:39,542 --> 00:57:41,795
Sang Ah.

671
00:57:41,795 --> 00:57:43,792
Sang Ah.

672
00:57:43,792 --> 00:57:45,553
Sang Ah.

673
00:58:05,918 --> 00:58:07,867
Sang Ah.

674
00:58:08,626 --> 00:58:10,536
Sang Ah.

675
00:58:12,584 --> 00:58:13,918
Sang Ah.

676
00:58:13,918 --> 00:58:15,750
Sang Ah.

677
00:58:31,042 --> 00:58:32,585
Sang Ah, stay with me.

678
00:58:32,585 --> 00:58:35,394
Sang Ah!

679
00:58:59,069 --> 00:59:01,671
Where am I?

680
00:59:05,331 --> 00:59:08,090
Are you with me?

681
00:59:08,090 --> 00:59:09,971
Are you okay?

682
00:59:14,096 --> 00:59:16,644
Is this hell?

683
00:59:44,626 --> 00:59:46,632
Yeah...

684
00:59:48,837 --> 00:59:50,970
It's hell.

685
01:02:04,930 --> 01:02:08,149
Ladies and gentlemen,
the moment you've been waiting for.

686
01:02:09,048 --> 01:02:11,539
Please welcome Candidate Bang Tae Seop

687
01:02:11,539 --> 01:02:14,209
and his lifelong partner,

688
01:02:14,209 --> 01:02:16,535
actress Chu Sang Ah!

689
01:04:33,036 --> 01:04:38,976
[To our climax: shattered, but never broken]
